#   DIFF-004: clickable difflet URIs â€” `diff:<path>?<from>..<to>#L<n>`

Clicking a diff hunk's nav link (e.g. `diff:ast/BAST.c#L362`) gives "be: no
results".  The hunk's click-target URI is built with an EMPTY query
(`graf/WEAVE.c` ~861/961: `HUNKu8sMakeURI(..,name,empty,line)` â†’ `diff:<path>#L`),
so clicking runs *wt-vs-base* (`beagle/BE.cli.c:251`) â€” empty for a committed
file.  `diff:`'s range form `?from#to` spends the fragment on `<to>`, leaving no
room for `#L`.  The `weave` verb already takes a `..` range in the QUERY
(`graf/GRAF.exe.c:483-493`), freeing the fragment.  Adopt that for `diff:`:
clickable difflets become `diff:<path>?<from>..<to>#L<n>`.  Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Nav-URI is the per-hunk `U` click target bro renders; today it omits the
    version â†’ wt-vs-base â†’ "no results" on a committed file (pre-existing;
    DIFF-003 `eaa75793` made file diffs worth clicking, exposing it).
 -  `diff:` range = `?from#to` (query=from, *fragment=to*) â€” no room for `#L`.
    `weave file?from..to` (GRAF.exe.c:483-493) puts both refs in the query.
 -  Repro: `be diff:graf/WEAVE.c#L100` â†’ empty; `be diff:graf/WEAVE.c?<from>..<to>`
    (range in query) leaves the fragment free for `#L`.

### Goals
 -  `diff:` accepts `?<from>..<to>` (range via `..` in the query); the fragment
    is the line anchor `#L<n>` (jump), not the range `to`.
 -  Diff hunks emit clickable nav URIs `diff:<path>?<from>..<to>#L<hunk_line>`;
    clicking opens the file-scoped (whole-file, DIFF-003) diff at that line.
 -  wt-vs-base hunks keep `diff:<path>#L<n>` (no query â€” correct, file is dirty).
 -  Commit-show (`diff:?<sha>` â†’ `GRAFDiffTreeRefs(parent,sha)`) per-file nav =
    `diff:<path>?<parent>..<sha>#L<n>`.

### Constraints
 -  Reuse the `weave` verb's `..` split (GRAF.exe.c:483-493) â€” do NOT reinvent.
 -  Guard the bare `?..` parent-branch relative form (`URI.mkd:42`): the split
    must not fire on a relative `..`/`?./x` ref.
 -  Producer/renderer split: graf emits the URI (data); bro owns the click +
    `#L` jump (existing fragment handling).  `abc/` untouched.

##  WIP

### Design decisions (settled with user 2026-06-15)
 -  URI form `diff:<path>?<from>..<to>#L<n>` chosen over `?from#to:L<n>` (the
    `#sym:L` overload) â€” it matches the live `weave` form and keeps the fragment
    purely a line anchor.  Legacy `?from#to` may stay as a fallback when the
    query has no `..` (back-compat), but `..` is the canonical range.

